Is it recognized with an Eco-Label ?
There might be a need in the form here to have a list of recognized label that are accepted on this platform.

column53: 1. Product is 100% made of material extracted from European ground
column54: 2. Product is 100% designed & manufactured in Europan factories & offices
column55: 3. Storage & distribution is 100% done from & to locations in Europe.
column56: 4. The product is plan to be exclusively used in Europe (i.e assumption of if it is expected customer could use this product mainly in Europe or the purpose if mostly for a use outside of Europe. This is obviously an assumption).
column57: 5. The Product will end-up in a end-of-life facility (i.e recycle company) located in Europe.
column58: 1. Contains no chemicals nocive for the environment in the product
column59: 2. Product packaging is either reusable at least a couple times, at least 80% recyclable or 100% biodegradable.
column60: 3. Product is either long-lasting (I.e could be used for years without the need to replace it), easily reparable (i.e we can find easily parts to repair it and repair it is cheaper than buying new oen) or quickly biodegradable.
column61: 4. Product is sustainable (i.e either organic, recycled-material based, or plant-material based).
column62: 5. The use of this product is sustainable (i.e. the product helps reducing the impact on the environment, for example it produces renwable energy or reduce CO2 emissions).
column63: 1. No testing or abuse on animals were involved during the entire product lifecycle.
column64: 2. No children work was involved during the entire product lifecycle.
column65: 3. Working conditions (salary, hours, rights) for workers involved during the entire product lifecycle were good
column66: 4. Good health & safety measures for workers were implemented during the entire product lifecycle
column67: 5. Workers didn't face any form of discrimination during the entire product lifecycle.
column72: 1. 100% of the service is created in European offices (Research, Development, Design).
column73: 2. 100% of the products needed to deliver the service is made in European factories & offices.
column74: 3. 100% of the Administration of the service is done in European locations (e.g. marketing, communication, support)
column75: 4. 100% of the service is delivered in Europe (example kayak lessons done on Lake Leman, Switzerland)
column76: 5. 100% of the products used to deliver the services will end-up in a end-of-life facility (i.e recycle company) located in Europe.
column77: 1. Products/Material used for delivery the service contain no chemicals nocive for the environment.
column78: 2. Product/Material packaging is either reusable at least a couple times, at least 80% recyclable or 100% biodegradable.
column79: 3. Service can be used As-Is for a long time reusing the same products or materials several times
column80: 4. Service is sustainable (i.e products or materials used are either organic, recycled-material based, or plant-based, or the service has no or low impact on the environment)
column81: 5. The use of this service is sustainable (i.e. it helps reducing the impact on the environment, for example you using eco-friendly products for cleaning services).
column82: 1. No testing or abuse on animals were involved during the entire service lifecycle.
column83: 2. No children work was involved during the entire service lifecycle.
column84: 3. Working conditions (salary, hours, rights) for workers involved during the entire service lifecycle were good
column85: 4. Good health & safety measures for workers were implemented during the entire service lifecycle
column86: 5. Workers didn't face any form of discrimination during the entire service lifecycle.
